# HTTP Request

An HTTP Request is sent by the client to request resources from a server.

Example:

GET /students HTTP/1.1

Host: localhost:8080

The client is requesting student data.

---

# HTTP Response

An HTTP Response is sent by the server.

It contains:

- Status Code
- Headers
- Response Body

Example:

HTTP/1.1 200 OK

Content-Type: application/json

---

# HTTP Methods

## GET

Retrieves data from the server.

Example:

GET /students

Returns all students.

---

## POST

Creates a new resource.

Example:

POST /students

Creates a new student.

---

## PUT

Updates an entire existing resource.

Example:

PUT /students/5

Updates all details of Student 5.

---

## PATCH

Updates only specific fields of a resource.

Example:

PATCH /students/5

Updates only the student's marks.

---

## DELETE

Deletes a resource.

Example:

DELETE /students/5

Deletes Student 5.

---

# CRUD Mapping

