# HTTP Status Codes

## 200 OK

Request completed successfully.

---

## 201 Created

A new resource was successfully created.

Usually returned after a POST request.

---

## 204 No Content

Request successful but no content is returned.

Usually returned after DELETE.

---

## 400 Bad Request

The client sent invalid data.

Example:

Missing required fields.

---

## 401 Unauthorized

Authentication is required.

Example:

User is not logged in.

---

## 403 Forbidden

Authentication succeeded, but the user does not have permission.

Example:

Student trying to access Admin APIs.

---

## 404 Not Found

The requested resource does not exist.

Example:

Student ID not found.

---

## 500 Internal Server Error

An unexpected error occurred on the server.

Example:

NullPointerException inside Spring Boot.

